OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FTens of thousands of people are
OL,7,Fexpected to descend on the capital on
OL,8,FSaturday for two major demonstrations
OL,9,Famid a huge #4.5 million police
OL,10,Foperation.
OL,12,FArmoured vehicles, police horses,
OL,13,Fdogs, drones and helicopters will be
OL,14,Fdeployed along with thousands of
OL,15,Fofficers as the Met aims to avoid
OL,16,Fclashes between Tommy Robinson's Unite
OL,17,Fthe Kingdom march and the pro-
OL,18,FPalestine Nakba Day rally.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FProsecutors have been told to consider
OL,7,Fwhether protest placards, banners and
OL,8,Fchants viewed on social media may
OL,9,Famount to offences of stirring up
OL,10,Fhatred during the rallies.
OL,12,FThe new guidance, issued before what
OL,13,Fpolice have described as an
OL,14,F"unprecedented" security operation,
OL,15,Furges prosecutors to assess whether
OL,16,Fslogans, symbols or chants may
OL,17,Finfluence audiences online if they are
OL,18,Ffilmed and shared.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FThe Crown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,7,Fsaid the revised advice is designed to
OL,8,Freflect "the changing international
OL,9,Fcontext" and follows separate guidance
OL,10,Fconcerning the fast-tracking of hate
OL,11,Fcrime prosecutions issued earlier this
OL,12,Fmonth.
OL,14,FThe guidance tells prosecutors to take
OL,15,Faccount of the wider context
OL,16,Fsurrounding protests, including
OL,17,Fheightened tensions linked to national
OL,18,For international events.
OL,26,@pD@IOUqD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FRecent criminal cases have seen
OL,7,Fsuspects charged after shouting "death
OL,8,Fto the IDF (Israel Defence Forces)"
OL,9,Fand "globalise the intifada".
OL,11,FDirector of Public Prosecutions
OL,12,FStephen Parkinson said: "This is not
OL,13,Fabout restricting free speech. It is
OL,14,Fabout preventing hate crime and
OL,15,Fprotecting the public, particularly at
OL,16,Fa time of heightened tensions.
OL,18,F"Where the line into criminality is
OL,19,Fcrossed, we will not hesitate to
OL,20,Fprosecute."
OL,26,@oD@aOUpD@cO]qD@EOUqD@\O]tD@YOUzD@AOU|D@
OL,26,AKO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FThe CPS said offences of stirring up
OL,7,Fhatred under the Public Order Act 1986
OL,8,Fcarry maximum prison sentences of
OL,9,Fseven years.
OL,11,FThe Government has also blocked 11
OL,12,Fforeign nationals described by Sir
OL,13,FKeir Starmer as "far-right agitators"
OL,14,Ffrom entering the UK ahead of the
OL,15,FUnite the Kingdom rally.
OL,26,@uD@QOUuD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FRight-wing figures claiming to have
OL,7,Fbeen barred include Polish politician
OL,8,FDominik Tarczynski, Belgian politician
OL,9,FFilip Dewinter, anti-Islam commentator
OL,10,FValentina Gomez and Dutch activist Eva
OL,11,FVlaardingerbroek.
OL,13,FSpeaking during a visit to a
OL,14,FMetropolitan Police command centre in
OL,15,FLambeth on Friday, the Prime Minister
OL,16,Fsaid the Unite the Kingdom organisers
OL,17,Fwere "peddling hatred and division,
OL,18,Fplain and simple".
OL,26,@yD@FOUzD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FHe added: "We will block those coming
OL,7,Finto the UK who seek to incite hatred
OL,8,Fand violence. For anyone who sets out
OL,9,Fto wreak havoc on our streets, to
OL,10,Fintimidate or threaten anyone, you can
OL,11,Fexpect to face the full force of the
OL,12,Flaw."
OL,14,FSir Keir carried out his visit to
OL,15,FLambeth alongside Met Commissioner Sir
OL,16,FMark Rowley and London Mayor Sir Sadiq
OL,17,FKhan before the weekend rallies.
OL,26,@nD@KOUtD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FSir Mark, while seated in the gold
OL,7,Fcommand suite in front of live CCTV
OL,8,Fimages of different parts of the
OL,9,Fcapital, told Sir Keir: "We've got a
OL,10,Ftime when hate crime has been
OL,11,Fescalated for the last two or three
OL,12,Fyears."
OL,14,FHe added: "And then 'small p' politics
OL,15,Fand protest groups who have got more
OL,16,Fpolarised and angry, and so both
OL,17,Fgroups at the weekend have a track
OL,18,Frecord of having an intimidatory
OL,19,Feffect on the communities."
OL,26,@qD@YOUtD@GO]vD@KOU{D@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FCommander Clair Haynes also told the
OL,7,FPrime Minister that drones would be
OL,8,Fused to monitor both protest routes
OL,9,Ffor "potential clashes or flashes"
OL,10,Fwhile officers in Wembley would
OL,11,Fmonitor CCTV feeds from the FA Cup
OL,12,Ffinal to identify supporters
OL,13,Ftravelling towards demonstrations.
OL,15,FFor the first time under official
OL,16,Fprotest restrictions, organisers of
OL,17,Fthe rallies will face prosecution as
OL,18,Fwell as any speakers who break the law
OL,19,Fby using the events as a platform for
OL,20,Fextremism or hate speech.
OL,26,@qD@EOUqD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779005164
OL,3,C'Unprecedented' police operation in
OL,4,Ccapital as tens of thousands to protest
OL,6,FLive facial recognition will be used
OL,7,Ffor the first time in a protest
OL,8,Fpolicing operation, with cameras set
OL,9,Fup in an area of Camden that is not on
OL,10,Fthe route of the Unite the Kingdom
OL,11,Fmarch, but is expected to be used by a
OL,12,Flot of people attending the event.
OL,14,FThe Biometrics and Surveillance Camera
OL,15,FCommissioner Professor William Webster
OL,16,Ftold the Press Association police
OL,17,Fforces could find themselves taken to
OL,18,Fcourt over their use of the
OL,19,Ftechnology, saying it is not
OL,20,F"foolproof".
OL,26,@|D@AOU|D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
